  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Auroville, India: Support a Tree in the Bio-region</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">We regenerate land by planting forests of native species of which 95% were destroyed due to human pressure. Such species are resilient to a changing climate and will be invaluable for preserving biodiversity and recharging aquifers. They also support local wildlife such as insects, birds and mammals. 15000 plants of over 100 species will be planted and protected on 15 acres of degraded land over a period of 8 years. These forests are planted using natural succession techniques.</narrative>
  </description>
